*******************************************************************************
 
              An alternative to tetramer based fingerprinting.

*******************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************

The basic idea is that you call ORFs using prodigal, GeneMark etc. Then you
calculate a codon usage profile for the entire contig based only on the
sequences of the ORFs within that contig. This software is a collection of
scripts which work in the following way:

        cub.pl                 -- Main wrapper
    	squishOrfs.pl          -- Put all the orfs from each contig into 1 lump
        barcodeByCU.pl         -- Create barcode from the squished fasta file

I wouldn't predict that this approach would work well on a set of Genes as each
gene is likely to display a CU profile based more on functionality, rather than
origin. However YMMV... I have written this software as part of a broader
bininng pipeline which takes long (>5KB) microbial contigs as input.

    Relies on other repos:
    
    gff2fasta.pl    http://github.com/minillinim/gff2fasta
    callOrfs.pl     http://github.com/minillinim/callOrfs
    
